title: Derive Nicod's Axiom from Lukasiewicz's First Sheffer Stroke Axiom

blocks.name: lukshef-ax1
blocks.content: This alternative axiom for propositional calculus using the Sheffer Stroke was discovered by Lukasiewicz in his Selected Works. It improves on Nicod's axiom by reducing its number of variables by one. This axiom also uses ~ nic-mp for its constructions. Here, the axiom is proved as a substitution instance of ~ nic-ax . (Contributed by Anthony Hart, 31-Jul-2011.) (Proof modification is discouraged.) (New usage is discouraged.)

blocks.origin:
thm lukshefth2(wff w0, wff w1) {
  |- wnan(wnan(w0, w1), wnan(wnan(w1, w0), wnan(w1, w0)))
} = {
  nic-mp(wnan(wnan(w0, w1), wnan(wnan(w1, w0), wnan(w1, w0))), wnan(w1, wnan(w1, w1)), wnan(w0, wnan(w0, w0)))
  nic-mp(wnan(w1, wnan(w1, w1)), wnan(wnan(w1, wnan(w1, wnan(w1, w1))), wnan(wnan(wnan(hw0, wnan(hw1, hw2)), w1), wnan(wnan(hw0, wnan(hw1, hw2)), w1))), wnan(wnan(w0, hw2), wnan(wnan(hw2, w0), wnan(hw2, w0))))
  nic-mp(wnan(wnan(w1, wnan(w1, wnan(w1, w1))), wnan(wnan(wnan(hw0, wnan(hw1, hw2)), w1), wnan(wnan(hw0, wnan(hw1, hw2)), w1))), wnan(wnan(hw0, wnan(hw1, hw2)), wnan(wnan(w1, wnan(w1, w1)), wnan(wnan(w1, hw1), wnan(wnan(hw0, w1), wnan(hw0, w1))))), wnan(w1, wnan(w1, w1)))
  lukshef-ax1(hw0, hw1, hw2, w1)
  lukshef-ax1(wnan(hw0, wnan(hw1, hw2)), wnan(w1, wnan(w1, w1)), wnan(wnan(w1, hw1), wnan(wnan(hw0, w1), wnan(hw0, w1))), w1)
  nic-mp(wnan(wnan(wnan(w1, wnan(w1, wnan(w1, w1))), wnan(wnan(wnan(hw0, wnan(hw1, hw2)), w1), wnan(wnan(hw0, wnan(hw1, hw2)), w1))), wnan(wnan(wnan(w0, hw2), wnan(wnan(hw2, w0), wnan(hw2, w0))), wnan(w1, wnan(w1, w1)))), wnan(wnan(wnan(wnan(w0, hw2), wnan(wnan(hw2, w0), wnan(hw2, w0))), wnan(w1, wnan(w1, w1))), wnan(hw2, wnan(hw2, hw2))), wnan(wnan(wnan(w1, wnan(w1, wnan(w1, w1))), wnan(wnan(wnan(hw0, wnan(hw1, hw2)), w1), wnan(wnan(hw0, wnan(hw1, hw2)), w1))), wnan(wnan(wnan(w0, hw2), wnan(wnan(hw2, w0), wnan(hw2, w0))), wnan(w1, wnan(w1, w1)))))
  lukshefth1(w0, hw2, hw2, w1, hw2)
  nic-mp(wnan(wnan(wnan(wnan(wnan(w0, hw2), wnan(wnan(hw2, w0), wnan(hw2, w0))), wnan(w1, wnan(w1, w1))), wnan(hw2, wnan(hw2, hw2))), wnan(wnan(wnan(wnan(w1, wnan(w1, wnan(w1, w1))), wnan(wnan(wnan(hw0, wnan(hw1, hw2)), w1), wnan(wnan(hw0, wnan(hw1, hw2)), w1))), wnan(wnan(wnan(w0, hw2), wnan(wnan(hw2, w0), wnan(hw2, w0))), wnan(w1, wnan(w1, w1)))), wnan(wnan(wnan(w1, wnan(w1, wnan(w1, w1))), wnan(wnan(wnan(hw0, wnan(hw1, hw2)), w1), wnan(wnan(hw0, wnan(hw1, hw2)), w1))), wnan(wnan(wnan(w0, hw2), wnan(wnan(hw2, w0), wnan(hw2, w0))), wnan(w1, wnan(w1, w1)))))), wnan(wnan(wnan(w1, wnan(w1, wnan(w1, w1))), wnan(wnan(wnan(hw0, wnan(hw1, hw2)), w1), wnan(wnan(hw0, wnan(hw1, hw2)), w1))), wnan(wnan(hw2, wnan(hw2, hw2)), wnan(wnan(hw2, wnan(wnan(hw0, wnan(hw1, hw2)), w1)), wnan(wnan(wnan(w1, wnan(w1, wnan(w1, w1))), hw2), wnan(wnan(w1, wnan(w1, wnan(w1, w1))), hw2))))), wnan(wnan(wnan(wnan(w0, hw2), wnan(wnan(hw2, w0), wnan(hw2, w0))), wnan(w1, wnan(w1, w1))), wnan(wnan(wnan(wnan(w0, hw2), wnan(wnan(hw2, w0), wnan(hw2, w0))), wnan(w1, wnan(w1, w1))), wnan(wnan(wnan(w0, hw2), wnan(wnan(hw2, w0), wnan(hw2, w0))), wnan(w1, wnan(w1, w1))))))
  lukshef-ax1(wnan(w1, wnan(w1, wnan(w1, w1))), wnan(wnan(hw0, wnan(hw1, hw2)), w1), wnan(wnan(hw0, wnan(hw1, hw2)), w1), hw2)
  lukshef-ax1(wnan(wnan(w1, wnan(w1, wnan(w1, w1))), wnan(wnan(wnan(hw0, wnan(hw1, hw2)), w1), wnan(wnan(hw0, wnan(hw1, hw2)), w1))), wnan(hw2, wnan(hw2, hw2)), wnan(wnan(hw2, wnan(wnan(hw0, wnan(hw1, hw2)), w1)), wnan(wnan(wnan(w1, wnan(w1, wnan(w1, w1))), hw2), wnan(wnan(w1, wnan(w1, wnan(w1, w1))), hw2))), wnan(wnan(wnan(w0, hw2), wnan(wnan(hw2, w0), wnan(hw2, w0))), wnan(w1, wnan(w1, w1))))
  lukshef-ax1(w1, w1, w1, w0)
}

blocks.name: renicax
blocks.content: A rederivation of ~ nic-ax from ~ lukshef-ax1 , proving that ~ lukshef-ax1 with ~ nic-mp can be used as a complete axiomatization of propositional calculus. (Contributed by Anthony Hart, 31-Jul-2011.) (Proof modification is discouraged.) (New usage is discouraged.)
